 SHADE.APP =C2=B7 DESIGN SYSTEM
UI Design Plan

Complete visual design specification for *Shade* =E2=80=94 the digital pet =
app that
feels your world
*App Name: Shade* =E2=80=94 a dual meaning at its core. A *shade* is a them=
e, a
visual skin, a mood. But Shade is also what the pet gives you when you've
been neglecting it. The name lives in both the design system and the
personality of the app.
01 =C2=B7 Design Philosophy

The UI is not a wrapper around the pet =E2=80=94 *it is the pet's world.* E=
very
Shade makes Mochi feel like it belongs to a different universe while
keeping the core emotional contract intact: the pet lives in your phone, it
notices your life, and it has opinions about it.
=F0=9F=8E=AD
Character first
Every screen makes the pet feel like a real personality, not a stat tracker
=F0=9F=93=B1
Glanceable
The most important info visible in under 2 seconds on every screen
=E2=9C=A8
Shareable moments
Every screen has at least one element designed to be screenshot-worthy
02 =C2=B7 The Shade System

5 Shades ship in v1. Each is a complete design system =E2=80=94 typography,=
 color,
spacing, and component style all change together. Users pick a Shade at
onboarding and can switch anytime from Settings. The active Shade also
styles the pet's weekly Instagram story card, so every share looks unique.
Y2K GLITCH
Dark =C2=B7 Pixel art =C2=B7 CRT energy
OLED black with cyan + pink + yellow neon. Scanline overlay. Press Start 2P
+ VT323 typefaces. Pixel art stat bars. Feels like a bootleg Tamagotchi on
a hacked console.
#00FFEE #FF2D78 #FFEE00 #9B00FF
SOFT DARK
Purple =C2=B7 Glassmorphism =C2=B7 Editorial
Deep purple-black, lavender + rose pastels. Instrument Serif italic
headlines. Frosted glass cards. The pet feels like it lives in a late-night
journal entry.
#C4B5FD #F4A0B5 #FBBF8A
FOREST
Deep green =C2=B7 Organic =C2=B7 Calm
Dark forest greens with mint accents. Playfair Display serif. Your pet
lives in a quiet mossy terrarium. For users who want calm over chaos.
#86EFCA #4ADE80 #D4F0E0
SUNSET
Burnt orange =C2=B7 Bold type =C2=B7 Raw energy
Charred black with amber + burnt orange. Bebas Neue all-caps. Sharp edges.
Feels like a vintage sci-fi paperback. Bold, loud, opinionated.
#FF6B35 #FBBF24 #FFE0C8
PAPER
Warm cream =C2=B7 Serif =C2=B7 Literary
The only light Shade. Warm parchment base, sienna accents. Playfair italic.
Feels like reading your pet's diary on aged paper.
#F5F0E8 #8B4513 #2A1F0F
03 =C2=B7 Screen Inventory
Screen Purpose Priority
Splash / Boot App open animation, pet waking up, active Shade loads v1
Onboarding Name pet, pick voice, choose your first Shade v1
Home Pet viewport, sensor chips, vitals, latest post v1
Check-In Modal Pet reacts to what happened since last visit v1
Feed All pet posts, shareable story cards v1
Story Card Generator Weekly Instagram export, styled to active Shade v1
Stats / History Sensor charts, mood trends, notable days v1
Shade Picker Live theme switcher =E2=80=94 5 Shades, instant preview v1
Milestone Cards Day 7, 30, 100 celebration screens =E2=80=94 shareable v1
Year-End Letter Full-screen cinematic Dec 31 experience v1 Pro
Nearby Encounters Bluetooth pet meeting screen, encounter history v2 04 =C2=
=B7
Pet Animation States
State Trigger Description
Idle Default Gentle float, blink, breathing
Happy High mood, good steps Bouncing, tail wag, sparkles
Sad Long neglect, low mood Drooping, single tear, slow movement
Startled Phone drop, sudden shake Jump, sweat drop, wide eyes
Sleepy Dark environment, late night Half-closed eyes, ZZZ bubbles
Hungry Battery < 15% Grabs stomach, stressed movement
Fed Plugged in to charge Runs to bowl, happy eating animation
Giving Shade =F0=9F=98=82 Grudge state post-neglect Facing away, arms cross=
ed,
ignores taps 05 =C2=B7 Flutter Implementation Notes

   - Shade system via *ThemeData + InheritedWidget* =E2=80=94 full hot-swap=
,
   persisted via SharedPreferences
   - Pet animations via *Rive* =E2=80=94 state machine with 8 named states
   - Story card export via *RepaintBoundary =E2=86=92 PNG =E2=86=92 share_p=
lus*
   - Sensor chips update every foreground via *WidgetsBindingObserver*
   - Story cards inherit the active Shade =E2=80=94 same palette, same font=
s,
   social-optimised layout
   - All dark Shades use true *AMOLED black (#000000)* for battery savings
   - Accessibility: 4.5:1 contrast minimum, haptic feedback on all pet
   interactions

06 =C2=B7 Next Design Steps
*Week 1:* Pet character illustration =E2=80=94 all 8 states drawn, handed t=
o Rive
animator
*Week 2:* Build Shade system in Flutter =E2=80=94 all 5 Shades coded, live =
switcher
working
*Week 3:* Home screen + Check-In modal =E2=80=94 pet reacts to sensor snaps=
hot on
open
*Week 4:* Story card generator + Feed =E2=80=94 Claude API pipeline produce=
s themed
post cards
*Week 5=E2=80=936:* Onboarding, Shade Picker, Stats =E2=80=94 full app shel=
l, ready for
internal test
